<br>
There are two ways of thinking about it.  On the one hand you can call if profiteering.  On the other hand you can call it an open market and market forces at work.  I know a lot of people who are just as happy to sell their stuff cheap because they don't have the time/bank space/patience to sit there and sell it for more.  In those cases having me (or someone else) buy it to resell it is the best thing in the world for them.  They are just as happy to move on.<br>
<br>
I've got a simple policy.  And I've made this offer to many people but I've yet to have ANYONE take me up on it.  If I buy something from you, and mark it up, or even if you happen to send me a tell and note that I'm a regular customer or whatever, I'll be upfront and say &quot;Hey, I'm reselling this.  If that bothers you, let me know.  I'll return this for what I paid, if you want, and I'll remember not to buy from you again except for personal use.&quot;  I've received nothing but praise for making the offer, and no one has yet accepted.<br>
<br>
Seriously, we are all at the mercy of the market.  If you don't like people reselling...well, you don't like capitalism.  And honestly, I don't either.  But the only way to change capitalism is to impose controls, and that option doesn't exist in EQ.  And at least in this capitalism no one goes hungry, cold, without proper shelter or medical care.  In short, there is no real poverty and no real &quot;needs&quot; going unfulfilled, just a whole lot of &quot;wants&quot; going unfulfilled.<br>
<br>
So yes, I've resold before.  I was a demon for it in the early days.  But reselling or not the market will always adjust to what people are willing to pay for something.  That's the only standard there is.  And it isn't just a sharp and continuous inflation either.  Acrylia pieces are at a stable 25-30, down from a high of 45.  HQ cat pelts are often at 7-8 now, down from a high of 12-15.  Things can improve, that way, and I've seen some speculators get really burned, like the uy still trying to sell 120 HQ cat pelts for 17 each long after the market had dived beneath him.  Even got nailed myself on velium once, if that makes you feel any better.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
